<ol><li>Each time it touches the negative plate, the ball&nbsp;<b>gain some electrons</b>&nbsp;and becomes&nbsp;<b>negatively charged</b>.</li><li>It is then&nbsp;<b>repelled by the negative plate</b>&nbsp;and pulled across the to postivite plate.</li><li>When the contact is made, electrons on the ball&nbsp;<b>transfer to the positive plate</b>&nbsp;so the ball now becomes&nbsp;<b>positively charged</b>.</li><li>It is then&nbsp;<b>repelled back</b>&nbsp;to the negative plate to <b>repeat the cycle</b>.</li></ol>